      "title": "Sunday sourdough notes from my tiny kitchen",
      "content": "I finally got a loaf with the kind of blistered crust I kept seeing in photos. The biggest change was patience: a longer bulk ferment, a gentle coil fold, and preheating the Dutch oven until I stopped doubting the timer.\n\nNext experiment is adding roasted garlic and rosemary. What mix-ins have worked well for you?",
